original: Håkansson, Sven Emanuel, kyrkoherde, Vetlanda, f. 28/9/92 i Hossmo, Kalmar 1., av godsäg. Johan H. o. Anna Stangenberg. G. 22 m. Greta Hemberg. Barn: Gunnel f. 24, Nils Gunnar 27, Bertil 30. — Stud:ex. i Kalmar 12, teol. fil. ex. 14, teol. kand., prakt. teol. prov o. prästv. f, Växjö stift 19. V. kommin. i Hånger, v. pastor i Borgholm o. Berga, kommin. i Hakarp av Huskvarna past. 21, kyr-koh. i Kråksmåla 26, i Vetlanda sed. 410, kontr:pirost sed. 47. Ordf. i kyrko-fullm:. o. -skoUstyr., sekr. i Upp;s. krdstl. s’tud:förb. 16-17. Skr.: Ungt kyrkfolk (Växjö stifts hembygdskalender 311), Vägen hem (i Mannen, som kom: tillbalka 37), art., betraktelser samt bok-anmäln. i dagspressen o. relig. tidn. LVO 47.
translated: Håkansson, Sven Emanuel, clergyman, Vetlanda, born 28/9/92 in Hossmo, Kalmar County, son of landowner Johan H. and Anna Stangenberg. Married to Greta Hemberg in 1922. Children: Gunnel (born) in 1924, Nils Gunnar in 1927, Bertil in 1930. He passed his secondary school leaving examination in Kalmar in 1912, theological philosophy examination in 1914, theological candidate, practical theology exam and priest ordination from the Växjö diocese in 1919. Served as assistant vicar in Hånger, assistant pastor in Borgholm and Berga, curate in Hakarp, Huskvarna, from 1921, vicar in Kråksmåla from 1926, and in Vetlanda from 1940, and district provost since 1947. He was chairman of the church council and school board, secretary of the Uppsala diocese study association from 1916-1917. He wrote: "Young Church People" (in the Växjö diocese local history calendar), "The Way Home" (in the "Man who came back" publication from 1937), articles, reflections and book reviews in daily newspapers and religious magazines. Received the Order of Vasa in 1947.
